  "prompt": "When is the CA-CPT exam held?",
  "response": "The **CA-CPT (Common Proficiency Test)** was historically the entry-level examination for the Chartered Accountancy (CA) course in India, administered by the **Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI)**. However, it's important to note that as of **2017**, the CA-CPT has been replaced by the **CA Foundation** exam.\n\n### **CA Foundation Exam Schedule**\n\nThe **CA Foundation** exam is typically conducted **twice a year**, in:\n\n1. **May Session**\n2. **November Session**\n\n#### **Key Points:**\n\n- **Registration Deadlines:** ICAI usually announces the registration dates along with the exam schedules. It's crucial to keep an eye on the [ICAI official website](https://www.icai.org/) for the most accurate and updated information.\n  \n- **Exam Pattern:** The CA Foundation consists of four papers covering various subjects related to accounting, law, and quantitative aptitude.\n\n- **Eligibility:** Before appearing for the CA Foundation exam, ensure you meet the eligibility criteria set by ICAI, which generally includes completing your Class 12 education.\n\n### **Next Steps:**\n\n1. **Visit the ICAI Website:** Regularly check the [ICAI notifications page](https://www.icai.org/about-icai/update-notices.html) for updates on exam dates, registration deadlines, and other important information.\n\n2. **Prepare Accordingly:** Familiarize yourself with the syllabus and exam pattern to start your preparation well in advance.\n\n3. **Stay Updated:** Changes to schedules or formats can occur, so staying informed through official channels is essential.\n\nIf you're referring to a different **CA-CPT** exam outside of the Chartered Accountancy framework in India, please provide additional details so I can offer more specific information.",
